        "cmip6.atmoschem.photo_chemistry.overview": {
            "values": [
                "Photolysis rates are derived from a lookup table created from the Tropospheric Ultraviolet and Visible Radiation (TUV) model, as described in [Lamarque, J.F. et al., Geosci. Model Dev., 5, 369\u2013411, 2012]. The photolysis calculation uses a look-up table between 200 and 750 nm and online calculations for wavelengths < 200 nm. Changes in the ozone column, but not in the aerosol burden, impact photolysis rates. The impact of clouds on photolysis rates is parameterized following [Madronich, S., J. Geophys. Res., 92, 9740\u20139752, 1987].  "
            ]
